title: The Beatles: Last Night in Hamburg 1962 (1999)
description:

These performances, made on a portable reel-to-reel recorder, take listeners back to a time when the Beatles were about to become huge; they were still playing small clubs. The audio quality is poor, but still listenable. The BeatlesÃ¢â‚¬â„¢ raw energy, comes through loud and clear.

This album is devoted almost exclusively to covers; "I Saw Her Standing There" and "Ask Me Why" are among the few Lennon-McCartney originals. Early rock & roll songs are a major focus.

Although the Beatles sound like diamonds in the rough on these performances, they had clearly developed a very distinctive sound.

One of the best-known semi-official Beatles releases.
